  Cookies
%p
  Cookies are text files placed on your computer by most websites that are generally used to provide additional functionality to a website as well as collect standard Internet log information and visitor behavior information.
%p
  For further information about cookies generally, visit
  =link_to "https://www.allaboutcookies.org", "https://www.allaboutcookies.org.", style:'color:#FF9933'
%p
  How do we Use Cookies?
%p
  This Website uses cookies to improve your experience on this Website. Cookies are used to:
%p
  Keep you logged in (if you have an account and are logged in).
  Show your username when logged in.
  Make navigation of the Website more convenient by remembering what content you have viewed recently.
%p
  How to Manage Cookies
%p
  You can set your browser not to accept cookies, and the website https://www.allaboutcookies.org tells you how to remove cookies from your browser. However, this Website’s features mentioned above will not be available if you do this.
%p
  Do Not Track
%p
  Some web browsers may give you the ability to enable a "do not track" feature that sends signals to the websites you visit, indicating that you do not want your online activities tracked. This is different than blocking or deleting cookies, as browsers with a "do not track" feature enabled may still accept cookies. We currently do not respond to “do not track” signals.
%p
  How Long we Retain Your Information
%p
  All data is kept as long as needed to provide you Services or to comply with applicable law. This will normally be indefinitely, though sometimes older data will be deleted. If you delete your account, your account information (username, password and email address) will be deleted.
%p
  Business Transfers and Corporate Changes
%p
  We may share your Information with our subsequent owner, co-owner, or operator of one or more of the Services; or in connection with (including, without limitation, during the negotiation or due diligence process of) a corporate merger, consolidation, or restructuring; the sale of substantially all of our stock and/or assets; financing, acquisition, divestiture, or dissolution of all or a portion of our business; or other corporate change.
%p
  %strong YOUR RIGHTS IN RELATION TO THE INFORMATION WE COLLECT
%p
  You have the right to access, correct, delete, restrict processing, and object to processing of your information. If you wish to (i) update, alter, delete or obtain a copy of your information that we hold; (ii) restrict or stop us from using any of the information which we hold on you, including by withdrawing any consent you have previously given to the processing of such information; or (iii) where any information has been processed on the basis of your consent or as necessary to perform a contract to which you are a party, request a copy of such information in a suitable format, you can request this by emailing us at the address set out at the end of this Privacy Policy. We endeavor to respond to such requests within a month or less, although we reserve the right to extend this period for complex requests.
%p
  Please note that, if you request that we restrict or stop using information we hold on you, or withdraw a consent you have previously given to the processing of such information, this may affect our ability to provide Services to you or negatively impact the services we can provide to you. We reserve the right to deny you access for any reason permitted under applicable laws. Such exemptions may include national security, corporate finance and confidential references.
